WEBVTT

00:02.500 --> 00:03.920
KATARA: <i>Water...</i>

00:04.840 --> 00:06.130
<i>Earth...</i>

00:06.720 --> 00:08.640
<i>Fire...</i>

00:08.840 --> 00:10.180
<i>Air.</i>

00:11.350 --> 00:12.850
<i>Long ago...</i>

00:12.930 --> 00:14.680
<i>The four nations lived together
in harmony.</i>

00:14.770 --> 00:19.310
<i>Then everything changed
when the Fire Nation attacked.</i>

00:19.900 --> 00:23.780
<i>Only the Avatar, master of
all four elements could stop them.</i>

00:23.900 --> 00:25.440
<i>But when the world needed him most</i>

00:25.530 --> 00:27.610
<i>he vanished.</i>

00:27.700 --> 00:31.240
<i>100 years passed and my brother
and I discovered the new Avatar</i>

00:31.320 --> 00:32.870
<i>an airbender named Aang.</i>

00:33.200 --> 00:35.250
<i>And although his airbending
skills were great</i>

00:35.580 --> 00:37.790
<i>he has a lot to learn before
he's ready to save anyone.</i>

00:37.870 --> 00:39.000
AANG: Oof.

00:39.080 --> 00:43.090
<i>But I believe Aang can save the world.</i>

00:43.750 --> 00:45.510
( ♪... )

00:48.010 --> 00:50.470
( MAN READING )

00:50.760 --> 00:52.680
OZAI: I am proud of you, Prince Zuko.

00:52.890 --> 00:55.810
You slayed the Avatar.

00:57.020 --> 00:59.560
ZUKO: You're so beautiful
when you hate the world.

00:59.890 --> 01:01.730
I don't hate you.

01:01.810 --> 01:03.020
I don't hate you, too.

01:05.190 --> 01:07.650
I have everything I always wanted.

01:07.740 --> 01:09.610
But it's not at all
how I thought it would be.

01:09.700 --> 01:12.280
The Avatar is alive.

01:12.450 --> 01:13.580
I want you to find him...

01:13.950 --> 01:15.830
...And end him.

01:17.950 --> 01:21.620
( ♪... )

01:23.710 --> 01:25.750
( GROWLS )

01:25.960 --> 01:29.050
TY LEE: I'm so excited to spend
the weekend on Ember Island.

01:29.300 --> 01:32.260
It's gonna be great to hang out
on the beach and do nothing.

01:32.800 --> 01:34.470
Doing nothing is a waste of time.

01:34.550 --> 01:36.470
We're being sent away on
a forced vacation.

01:36.560 --> 01:37.640
I feel like a child.

01:37.720 --> 01:39.270
Lighten up.

01:39.350 --> 01:40.810
So dad wants to meet
with his advisors alone

01:40.890 --> 01:42.350
without anyone else around.

01:42.440 --> 01:44.110
Don't take it personally.

01:44.310 --> 01:47.150
Doesn't your family have
a house on Ember Island?

01:47.570 --> 01:49.440
We used to come every
summer when we were kids.

01:49.610 --> 01:51.030
That must've been fun.

01:51.450 --> 01:53.870
That was a long time ago.

02:05.380 --> 02:08.550
BOTH: Welcome to Ember Island, kids.

02:20.600 --> 02:22.560
It smells like old lady in here.

02:22.640 --> 02:23.900
Gee, I wonder why.

02:25.730 --> 02:27.690
TY LEE: Who are these two beautiful women?

02:27.900 --> 02:29.860
Can't you tell?

02:29.940 --> 02:31.690
- It's Li and me.
- It's Lo and me.

02:31.820 --> 02:33.280
( RETCHES )

02:33.610 --> 02:36.820
Ooh, I love this seashell bedspread.

02:36.910 --> 02:38.490
Are you serious?

02:38.580 --> 02:40.330
It looks like the beach
threw up all over it.

02:40.790 --> 02:42.910
LI: We know you're upset

02:43.000 --> 02:45.750
that you were forced
to come here this weekend.

02:45.830 --> 02:48.590
But Ember Island is a magical place.

02:49.210 --> 02:50.960
Keep an open mind.

02:51.050 --> 02:53.050
Give it a chance.

02:53.380 --> 02:56.470
And it can help you understand
yourselves and each other.

02:58.260 --> 03:01.020
The beach has a special way

03:01.100 --> 03:03.310
of smoothing even the most ragged edges.

03:04.270 --> 03:06.400
( YAWNS )

03:06.980 --> 03:09.480
BOTH: Time to hit the beach.

03:12.820 --> 03:14.820
TOPH: Aang, I know swimming is fun and all

03:14.900 --> 03:17.950
but do you really think you should be
exposing yourself like that?

03:18.070 --> 03:19.080
Cover up.

03:19.240 --> 03:21.290
What?
I'm wearing trunks.

03:21.490 --> 03:23.580
I know, it's your tattoos
I'm worried about.

03:23.660 --> 03:25.250
What if someone sees you?

03:25.330 --> 03:26.580
There are walls all around us.

03:26.670 --> 03:27.880
It's completely safe.

03:29.040 --> 03:31.000
( CHIRPS )

03:32.920 --> 03:33.970
AANG: Whoo, hey!

03:34.050 --> 03:36.880
( MOMO CHIRPS )

03:37.090 --> 03:40.720
( LAUGHING )

03:42.010 --> 03:45.600
This has got to be the most
boring job in the Fire Nation.

03:45.810 --> 03:47.730
- Nothing ever happens.
-( SNIFFS )

03:47.810 --> 03:49.940
AANG: Whoa!

03:53.230 --> 03:54.860
Let's go again.

04:00.370 --> 04:02.120
The Avatar's alive.

04:02.200 --> 04:04.290
We better send a messenger hawk
to the Fire Lord.

04:07.080 --> 04:08.080
( HAWK CRIES )

04:11.790 --> 04:13.210
A black ribbon message.

04:13.760 --> 04:15.720
This is so exciting.

04:15.800 --> 04:16.800
( LAUGHS )

04:34.780 --> 04:36.190
CHILDREN: Ahh!

04:37.240 --> 04:39.530
Hey, you need some help unpacking?

04:39.610 --> 04:42.120
- Sure, thanks.
-( GRUNTS )

04:52.710 --> 04:56.260
Could you scooch just
a little bit more to the...

04:56.800 --> 04:58.590
Perfect.

04:58.720 --> 05:00.470
( CHILD LAUGHS )

05:01.590 --> 05:02.680
Here...

05:02.760 --> 05:04.220
This is for you.

05:04.310 --> 05:06.180
Why would I want that?

05:06.270 --> 05:07.810
I saw it and I thought it was pretty.

05:08.020 --> 05:09.390
Don't girls like stuff like this?

05:09.600 --> 05:11.850
( SCOFFS ) Maybe stupid girls.

05:12.520 --> 05:13.520
Forget it!

05:23.240 --> 05:24.780
Wow, thanks.

05:24.870 --> 05:26.490
This is so pretty.

05:26.580 --> 05:28.160
Not as pretty as you are.

05:28.250 --> 05:30.120
That shell's not so great.

05:30.790 --> 05:32.750
Ahem, shade... Shade.

05:35.840 --> 05:38.050
I thought since it's so hot... Here.

05:39.920 --> 05:41.180
Thanks.

05:41.380 --> 05:43.300
This is really refreshing.

05:49.350 --> 05:51.230
Hey, beach bums, we're playing next.

05:51.310 --> 05:53.480
Ty lee, get over here now.

06:01.070 --> 06:04.370
( GIGGLING )

06:08.740 --> 06:10.790
See that girl with the silly pigtails?

06:11.000 --> 06:13.250
When she runs towards the ball

06:13.500 --> 06:15.210
there's just the slightest
hesitation of her left foot.

06:15.290 --> 06:17.590
I'm willing to bet a childhood
injury has weakened her.

06:17.670 --> 06:20.090
Keep serving the ball to her
left and we'll destroy her

06:20.170 --> 06:21.840
and the rest of her team.

06:22.090 --> 06:23.930
Dismissed.

06:53.160 --> 06:55.460
( FIRE CRACKLING )

06:55.670 --> 06:58.790
Yes, we defeated you for all time.

06:59.000 --> 07:02.090
You will never rise from the ashes of your
shame and humiliation.

07:03.260 --> 07:05.590
Well, that was fun.

07:05.680 --> 07:07.350
I'm having a party tonight.

07:07.550 --> 07:08.550
You should come by.

07:08.760 --> 07:09.760
Sure...

07:09.930 --> 07:11.060
I love parties.

07:11.390 --> 07:12.680
Your friend can come, too.

07:12.770 --> 07:15.390
Uh, what about me and my brother?

07:15.600 --> 07:17.190
Aren't you going to invite us?

07:17.520 --> 07:20.230
You don't know who we are, do you?

07:20.320 --> 07:22.230
Don't you know who we are?

07:22.440 --> 07:24.240
We're Chan and Ruon-Jian.

07:24.450 --> 07:25.450
Yeah.

07:27.570 --> 07:29.370
But fine, you're invited.

07:29.450 --> 07:31.410
Just so you know, though

07:31.620 --> 07:33.120
some of the most important teenagers in
the Fire Nation

07:33.330 --> 07:34.960
are gonna be at this party so...

07:35.160 --> 07:36.210
Try and act normal.

07:36.420 --> 07:37.710
We'll do our best.

07:44.170 --> 07:46.130
ZUKO: Why didn't you tell
those guys who we were?

07:46.220 --> 07:47.340
AZULA: I guess I was intrigued.

07:47.680 --> 07:49.600
I'm so used to people worshipping us.

07:49.720 --> 07:51.100
They should.

07:51.180 --> 07:53.140
Yes, I know, and I love it.

07:53.390 --> 07:55.350
But for once, I just wanted to see

07:55.430 --> 07:57.440
how people would treat us if
they didn't know who we were.

07:57.520 --> 07:59.440
Like waves washing away

07:59.520 --> 08:01.900
the footprints on the sand

08:02.150 --> 08:05.900
Ember island gives everyone a clean slate.

08:06.070 --> 08:08.700
Ember Island reveals the true you.

08:11.830 --> 08:13.700
- To the party.
- To the party.

08:13.790 --> 08:15.750
( HAWK CRIES )

08:18.670 --> 08:19.670
( CRYING CONTINUES )

08:22.800 --> 08:24.710
( SQUAWKING )

08:27.880 --> 08:28.880
( HAWK CRIES )

08:31.640 --> 08:34.520
( BIRDS CRYING )

08:58.460 --> 09:00.250
Um... You're a little early.

09:00.460 --> 09:01.540
No one's here yet.

09:01.750 --> 09:03.250
I heard you telling someone

09:03.340 --> 09:04.710
You'd be partying from dusk till dawn.

09:04.920 --> 09:07.210
It's dusk so we're here.

09:07.510 --> 09:10.130
But that's just an expression.

09:10.510 --> 09:12.470
We are the perfect party guests.

09:12.600 --> 09:14.640
We arrive right on time
because we are very punctual.

09:19.730 --> 09:21.230
CHAN: All right, listen,
my dad's an admiral.

09:21.310 --> 09:22.520
He has no idea I'm having this party

09:22.730 --> 09:24.520
so don't mess anything up.

09:26.440 --> 09:30.150
That's a sharp outfit, Chan... Careful.

09:30.280 --> 09:33.740
You could puncture the hull
of an Empire-class Fire Nation battleship

09:33.870 --> 09:36.040
leaving thousands to drown at sea...

09:36.540 --> 09:40.000
Because it's so sharp.

09:40.080 --> 09:43.290
Um... Thanks.

09:49.800 --> 09:52.300
Hey, first ones here, huh?

09:52.380 --> 09:56.010
He thinks he's so great.

09:56.220 --> 09:58.310
Well, what do you think of him?

09:58.520 --> 10:00.140
I don't have any opinion about him.

10:00.230 --> 10:01.810
I hardly know him.

10:01.890 --> 10:03.980
- You like him, don't you?
-( IRRITATED SIGH )

10:10.690 --> 10:12.660
So how do you know Ty Lee?

10:12.860 --> 10:14.910
I met her at the beach today.

10:14.990 --> 10:17.030
She was pretty impressed
by a sand pagoda that I made for her.

10:17.240 --> 10:20.450
Well, I met her first.

10:20.660 --> 10:24.080
Look, it doesn't matter
who I met first 'cause I like you all.

10:24.290 --> 10:26.210
But which one of us do you like?

10:26.420 --> 10:28.170
- Yeah.
- Tell us.

10:28.300 --> 10:30.050
I don't know, I don't know.

10:31.760 --> 10:32.840
( ALL GRUNT )

10:32.930 --> 10:33.930
ALL: Ooh.

10:34.010 --> 10:35.300
Ahh...

10:35.390 --> 10:37.260
Oh, I'm glad you're here.

10:37.350 --> 10:39.350
Those boys won't leave me alone.

10:39.430 --> 10:41.390
I guess they all just like me too much.

10:41.480 --> 10:44.440
Come on, Ty Lee,
you can't be this ignorant.

10:44.650 --> 10:46.520
What are you talking about?

10:46.730 --> 10:49.610
Those boys only like you because
you make it so easy for them.

10:49.820 --> 10:51.780
You're not a challenge-you're a tease.

10:51.990 --> 10:54.320
It's not like they
actually care who you are.

10:54.450 --> 10:56.030
( SOBBING )

10:56.320 --> 10:59.200
OK, OK, calm down.

10:59.410 --> 11:01.080
I didn't mean what I said.

11:01.160 --> 11:04.330
Look, maybe I just said it
because I was a little...

11:04.420 --> 11:05.420
( WHISPERS ) Jealous.

11:05.500 --> 11:07.380
What?

11:07.460 --> 11:09.420
You were jealous of me?

11:09.500 --> 11:13.340
Um, but, you're the most beautiful,
smartest, perfect girl in the world.

11:13.420 --> 11:14.970
Well, you're right about all those things.

11:15.180 --> 11:16.930
But for some reason when I meet boys

11:17.140 --> 11:19.390
they act as if I'm going to do
something horrible to them.

11:19.600 --> 11:22.560
( LAUGHS ) But you probably
would do something horrible to them.

11:22.770 --> 11:26.310
I'm sure they're just intimidated by you.

11:26.520 --> 11:28.560
OK, look, if you want a boy to like you

11:28.770 --> 11:30.570
just look at him and smile a lot

11:30.770 --> 11:33.490
and laugh at everything he says
even if it's not funny.

11:33.570 --> 11:38.030
Well, that sounds
really shallow and stupid.

11:38.240 --> 11:39.240
Let's try it.

11:39.410 --> 11:40.870
OK.

11:41.080 --> 11:42.870
( AS BOY ) "Hey, there, sweet sugar cakes.

11:43.080 --> 11:45.250
"How ya likin' this party?"

11:45.460 --> 11:47.540
( LAUGHS GIDDILY )

11:47.750 --> 11:49.340
( SILENCE )

11:49.540 --> 11:52.420
MAI: I'm bored.
ZUKO: I know.

11:52.500 --> 11:54.880
- I'm hungry.
- So what?

11:55.090 --> 11:56.840
So find me some food.

11:57.050 --> 11:58.050
Sure.

12:01.310 --> 12:03.720
Chan, I'm ready for a tour of the house.

12:07.810 --> 12:10.520
CHAN: Is this your first time
on Ember Island?

12:10.730 --> 12:13.070
AZULA: No, I used to come here years ago.

12:13.280 --> 12:15.650
It's a great place if you like sand.

12:15.860 --> 12:18.360
( LAUGHING )

12:18.450 --> 12:22.370
Yeah, it's like, "Welcome to Sandy Land."

12:22.580 --> 12:24.660
( BOTH LAUGH )

12:27.290 --> 12:30.750
Your arms look so strong.

12:30.960 --> 12:33.300
Yeah, I know.

12:36.800 --> 12:38.380
You're pretty.

12:38.470 --> 12:40.930
( SWEETLY ) Together, you and I will be...

12:41.140 --> 12:43.560
( FIRMLY ) The strongest couple
in the entire world.

12:43.640 --> 12:45.720
We will dominate the earth!

12:49.520 --> 12:51.940
Uh... I gotta go.

13:03.740 --> 13:05.740
Hey, watch it.

13:05.950 --> 13:07.660
That food was for my cranky girlfriend.

13:13.290 --> 13:14.300
Whoa...

13:15.920 --> 13:17.170
What are you doing?

13:17.380 --> 13:18.840
Stop talking to my girlfriend.

13:19.050 --> 13:21.300
Relax, it's just a party.

13:21.760 --> 13:22.760
Uh!

13:23.970 --> 13:26.520
Zuko, what is wrong with you?

13:26.600 --> 13:28.390
What's wrong with me?

13:28.600 --> 13:30.020
Your temper's out of control.

13:30.230 --> 13:32.020
You blow up over every little thing.

13:32.230 --> 13:35.070
You're so impatient and
hot-headed and angry.

13:35.270 --> 13:37.860
Well, at least I feel something...
As opposed to you.

13:38.070 --> 13:39.400
You have no passion for anything.

13:39.610 --> 13:42.160
You're just a big blah.

13:42.360 --> 13:44.530
It's over, Zuko.

13:44.740 --> 13:46.240
We're done.

13:46.450 --> 13:48.620
Who broke my Nana's vase?

13:50.580 --> 13:51.750
That's it, you're out of here.

13:51.960 --> 13:53.580
I was just leaving.

13:53.670 --> 13:56.380
Have fun by yourself, loser boy.

13:56.920 --> 13:58.130
Nice.

14:06.140 --> 14:08.310
( WAVES GENTLY ROLL )

14:19.490 --> 14:20.490
( CHILDREN SHRIEKING )

14:25.450 --> 14:27.120
( BIRD SINGS )

14:31.370 --> 14:33.620
( BABY CRIES )

15:04.860 --> 15:06.450
( BABY LAUGHS )

15:21.090 --> 15:22.170
( METALLIC CLANKING )

15:25.220 --> 15:27.220
Guys, you're all gonna think I'm crazy

15:27.430 --> 15:29.140
but it feels like a metal man is coming.

15:29.890 --> 15:32.430
( GROANS )

15:44.490 --> 15:45.570
( GRUNTS )

15:47.700 --> 15:48.700
( GROANS )

15:49.780 --> 15:51.080
( ALL SCREAM )

16:04.590 --> 16:05.590
( APPA ROARS )

16:15.600 --> 16:17.190
AZULA: I thought
I'd find you here.

16:17.270 --> 16:21.190
Those summers we spent
here seem so long ago.

16:21.270 --> 16:23.610
So much has changed.

16:23.690 --> 16:25.030
Come down to the beach with me.

16:25.490 --> 16:28.070
Come on, this place is depressing.

16:40.000 --> 16:41.210
Hey...

16:41.420 --> 16:43.090
Where's your new boyfriend?

16:46.420 --> 16:48.430
Are you cold?

16:48.840 --> 16:51.300
I'm freezing.

16:51.640 --> 16:53.390
I'll make a fire.

16:53.470 --> 16:56.850
ZUKO: There's plenty of
stuff to burn in there.

16:56.980 --> 16:57.980
( GROWLS )

17:00.810 --> 17:02.560
This is crazy.

17:02.650 --> 17:04.900
How can we beat a guy who blows
things up with his mind?

17:04.980 --> 17:05.980
We can.

17:06.150 --> 17:07.190
Jump on Appa.

17:07.280 --> 17:08.320
I'll try to distract him.

17:23.590 --> 17:26.050
( PANTING )

17:28.340 --> 17:31.220
( HEAVY FOOTSTEPS THUD )

17:39.180 --> 17:41.940
( HEAVY FOOTSTEPS CONTINUE )

18:23.190 --> 18:24.730
( APPA GROWLS )

18:24.940 --> 18:27.480
( SIGHS ) I'm OK.

18:27.690 --> 18:28.690
Well, that was random.

18:28.860 --> 18:30.440
I don't think so.

18:30.530 --> 18:33.240
I get the feeling he knows who we are.

18:33.450 --> 18:35.910
( FIRE CRACKLING )

18:38.410 --> 18:40.330
TY LEE: What are you doing?

18:40.410 --> 18:42.040
What does it look like I'm doing.

18:42.250 --> 18:44.580
But it's a painting of your family.

18:44.670 --> 18:45.670
You think I care?

18:45.750 --> 18:47.040
I think you do.

18:47.170 --> 18:50.840
You don't know me, so why don't
you just mind your own business?

18:51.260 --> 18:52.880
Ah, I know you.

18:53.090 --> 18:54.470
No, you don't.

18:54.550 --> 18:56.220
You're stuck in your little Ty Lee world

18:56.300 --> 18:57.930
where everything's great all the time.

18:58.010 --> 18:59.970
Zuko, leave her alone.

19:00.060 --> 19:01.810
( MOCKING ) I'm so pretty, look at me.

19:01.890 --> 19:03.810
I can walk on my hands, whoo!

19:07.440 --> 19:08.770
Circus freak.

19:08.980 --> 19:10.730
( LAUGHS )

19:10.940 --> 19:12.780
Yes, I'm a circus freak.

19:12.990 --> 19:14.820
Go ahead and laugh all you want.

19:14.990 --> 19:17.030
You wanna know why I joined the circus?

19:17.240 --> 19:18.830
Here we go.

19:18.910 --> 19:21.410
TY LEE: Do you have any idea
what my home life was like

19:21.500 --> 19:22.830
growing up with six sisters

19:22.910 --> 19:25.120
who look exactly like me?

19:25.250 --> 19:27.750
It was like,
I didn't even have my own name.

19:27.960 --> 19:29.460
I joined the circus because

19:29.670 --> 19:31.880
I was scared of spending
the rest of my life

19:32.090 --> 19:33.920
as part of a matched set.

19:34.130 --> 19:35.470
At least, I'm different now.

19:35.680 --> 19:38.470
Circus freak is a compliment.

19:38.680 --> 19:41.890
Guess that explains why you
need 10 boyfriends, too.

19:42.100 --> 19:43.640
I'm sorry, what?

19:43.850 --> 19:45.600
Attention issues?

19:45.810 --> 19:47.560
You couldn't get enough
attention when you were a kid

19:47.650 --> 19:50.110
so you're trying to make up for it now.

19:50.320 --> 19:53.320
Well, what's your excuse, Mai?

19:53.530 --> 19:55.530
You were an only child for 15 years.

19:55.610 --> 19:57.360
But even with all that attention

19:57.530 --> 20:00.450
your aura is this dingy, pasty, gray...

20:00.580 --> 20:02.910
I don't believe in auras.

20:02.990 --> 20:05.290
Yeah, you don't believe in anything.

20:05.370 --> 20:09.210
Oh, well, I'm sorry I can't be as
high-strung and crazy as the rest of you.

20:09.290 --> 20:11.210
ZUKO: I'm sorry, too.

20:11.290 --> 20:13.630
I wish you would be
high-strung and crazy for once

20:13.710 --> 20:16.130
instead of keeping all your
feelings bottled up inside.

20:16.220 --> 20:17.880
She just called your aura dingy.

20:18.140 --> 20:19.140
Are you gonna take that?

20:19.390 --> 20:21.300
What do you want from me?

20:21.390 --> 20:24.470
You want a teary confession
about how hard my childhood was?

20:24.770 --> 20:26.390
Well, it wasn't.

20:26.560 --> 20:29.190
I was a rich only child
who got anything I wanted

20:29.400 --> 20:31.400
as long as I behaved...

20:31.860 --> 20:34.150
...And sat still

20:34.360 --> 20:36.780
and didn't speak unless spoken to.

20:36.990 --> 20:39.660
My mother said I had
to keep out of trouble.

20:39.870 --> 20:41.990
We had my dad's political
career to think about.

20:42.200 --> 20:44.120
AZULA: Well, that's it, then.

20:44.330 --> 20:46.790
You had a controlling mother
who had certain expectations

20:46.870 --> 20:48.790
and if you strayed from them
you were shut down.

20:49.120 --> 20:51.330
That's why you're afraid
to care about anything

20:51.540 --> 20:52.540
and why you can't express yourself.

20:52.750 --> 20:54.670
You want me to express myself?

20:54.880 --> 20:55.880
Leave me alone!

20:58.430 --> 21:00.680
I like it when you express yourself.

21:00.890 --> 21:01.970
Don't touch me.

21:02.180 --> 21:04.390
I'm still mad at you.

21:04.600 --> 21:07.680
My life hasn't been that easy,
either, Mai.

21:07.770 --> 21:10.310
Whatever. That doesn't excuse the way
you've been acting.

21:10.650 --> 21:12.230
TY LEE: Calm down, you guys.

21:12.440 --> 21:14.650
This much negative energy
is bad for your skin.

21:14.730 --> 21:16.230
You'll totally break out.

21:16.320 --> 21:17.740
ZUKO: Bad skin?

21:17.820 --> 21:19.650
Normal teenagers worry about bad skin.

21:19.780 --> 21:21.660
I don't have that luxury.

21:21.740 --> 21:24.910
My father decided to teach me
a permanent lesson on my face.

21:25.580 --> 21:27.660
Sorry, Zuko, I...

21:27.750 --> 21:30.620
For so long, I thought
that if my dad accepted me, I'd be happy.

21:30.710 --> 21:31.710
I'm back home, now.

21:31.790 --> 21:33.080
My dad talks to me.

21:33.170 --> 21:35.380
Huh, he even thinks I'm a hero.

21:35.460 --> 21:36.800
Everything should be perfect, right?

21:36.880 --> 21:39.170
I should be happy now, but I'm not.

21:39.260 --> 21:41.720
I'm angrier than ever
and I don't know why.

21:42.180 --> 21:44.140
There's a simple question
you need to answer then.

21:44.600 --> 21:46.010
Who are you angry at?

21:46.100 --> 21:48.520
No one, I'm just angry.

21:48.600 --> 21:51.190
Yeah, who are you angry at, Zuko?

21:51.650 --> 21:54.190
Everyone... I don't know.

21:54.270 --> 21:55.320
Is it Dad?

21:55.400 --> 21:56.690
No, no.

21:56.900 --> 21:57.940
- Your uncle?
- Me?

21:58.150 --> 21:59.990
No, no... No, no.

22:00.200 --> 22:01.280
Then who?

22:01.490 --> 22:02.530
Who are you angry at?

22:02.610 --> 22:03.700
Answer the question, Zuko.

22:03.780 --> 22:05.120
TY LEE: Talk to us.

22:05.200 --> 22:06.200
MAI: Come on, answer the question.

22:06.280 --> 22:07.450
AZULA: Come on, answer it.

22:08.200 --> 22:10.460
ZUKO: I'm angry at myself.

22:15.460 --> 22:16.630
AZULA: Why?

22:16.840 --> 22:19.210
Because I'm confused.

22:19.300 --> 22:21.010
Because I'm not sure I know the difference

22:21.090 --> 22:22.550
between right and wrong anymore.

22:22.760 --> 22:24.010
You're pathetic.

22:24.470 --> 22:27.220
MAI: I know one thing I care about...

22:27.430 --> 22:28.850
I care about you.

22:30.890 --> 22:32.480
( LONE HAND CLAP )

22:32.560 --> 22:36.150
Well, those were wonderful
performances, everyone.

22:36.360 --> 22:39.230
I guess you wouldn't understand,
would you, Azula

22:39.440 --> 22:41.030
because you're just so perfect.

22:41.240 --> 22:43.320
Well, yes, I guess you're right.

22:43.410 --> 22:45.620
I don't have sob stories like all of you.

22:45.820 --> 22:48.580
I could sit here and complain how our mom
liked Zuko more than me

22:48.660 --> 22:51.410
but I don't really care.

22:51.620 --> 22:52.960
My own mother...

22:53.160 --> 22:54.750
Thought I was a monster.

22:58.000 --> 23:02.010
She was right, of course,
but it still hurt.

23:02.220 --> 23:04.470
TY LEE: What Lo and Li said came true.

23:04.680 --> 23:06.430
The beach did help us
learn about ourselves.

23:06.640 --> 23:08.720
I feel all smoothed.

23:08.810 --> 23:10.600
I'll always remember this.

23:10.680 --> 23:13.810
You know what would make
this trip really memorable?

23:17.730 --> 23:20.150
We've got some bad news, Chan.

23:20.360 --> 23:21.480
Party's over.

23:23.240 --> 23:24.740
( SCREAMING )

23:24.820 --> 23:25.820
( GRUNTS )

23:35.790 --> 23:36.790
( CRYING LOUDLY )

23:46.550 --> 23:48.090
( ♪... )

23:48.180 --> 23:50.100
( MEN VOCALIZING RHYTHMICALLY )
